external_knowledge:
- High-performing employees are those with a higher rating than the average rating of their department; 
- Tenure is calculated by subtracting the join date from the current date and is expressed in years; 
- A year is assumed to have 365 days for the sake of simplicity in calculating the 5-year threshold.

sql:
SELECT currency, AVG(annual_salary) AS average_salary
FROM employee_salaries
GROUP BY currency;

SELECT position_name 
FROM positions 
ORDER BY position_name;
